---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy — realpls" description="Your privacy matters. Learn how realpls handles your data (spoiler: it doesn't).">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="main container container-narrow">
    <article class="content">
      <header class="content-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Your images stay on your device. Always.
        </p>
      </header>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>The Short Version</h2>
        <div class="highlight-box">
          <div class="highlight-icon">
            <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M12 1L3 5V11C3 16.55 6.84 21.74 12 23C17.16 21.74 21 16.55 21 11V5L12 1Z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              <path d="M9 12L11 14L15 10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <ul>
              <li>✓ Your images are processed 100% locally in your browser</li>
              <li>✓ We never upload, store, or transmit your images</li>
              <li>✓ We don't use cookies or tracking scripts</li>
              <li>✓ We don't collect any personal information</li>
              <li>✓ There is no backend server that sees your data</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>How It Works</h2>
        <p>
          When you upload an image to realpls, the file is read directly by your web browser using the 
          <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/FileReader" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FileReader API</a>. 
          The image data is then processed using the 
          <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Canvas API</a> 
          to perform forensic analysis.
        </p>
        <p>
          All computation happens on your device. The image data never leaves your browser, never touches 
          our servers (because there aren't any for this purpose), and is discarded from memory when you 
          close the page or analyze a new image.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>What We Don't Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list">
          <li><strong>Images:</strong> We never see, store, or have access to the images you analyze</li>
          <li><strong>Personal data:</strong> No names, emails, accounts, or identification</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> We don't track which features you use or how long you stay</li>
          <li><strong>Device information:</strong> We don't fingerprint your browser or collect device details</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Static Hosting</h2>
        <p>
          This website is hosted as a static site on Cloudflare Pages. While Cloudflare may collect 
          standard web server logs (IP addresses, timestamps, etc.) as part of their service, this is 
          outside our control and governed by 
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          We don't have access to these logs and don't use any analytics or tracking services.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Downloaded Reports</h2>
        <p>
          The "Download JSON" feature generates a report file locally in your browser. This file is 
          created client-side and downloaded directly to your device. No data is sent to any server 
          during this process.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>External Resources</h2>
        <p>
          This site loads fonts from Google Fonts, which means Google may receive your IP address and 
          some browser information. This is standard practice for most websites. If this concerns you, 
          you can block Google Fonts using browser extensions or privacy tools.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          Don't take our word for it — the code is open for inspection. You can verify exactly what 
          the application does by reviewing the source code. There are no hidden network requests, 
          no telemetry, and no data collection mechanisms.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <section class="section">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy? Reach out at 
          <a href="https://swasilewski.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">swasilewski.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
      
      <div class="update-notice">
        <p>Last updated: December 2024</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="back-link">
        <a href="/">← Back to analyzer</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .main {
    flex: 1;
    padding-top: var(--space-10);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }
  
  .content {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    padding: var(--space-10);
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .content {
      padding: var(--space-6);
    }
  }
  
  .content-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-8);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .content-header h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  
  .section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }
  
  .section h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .section p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  
  .highlight-box {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    padding: var(--space-5);
    background: var(--color-ok-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-ok);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  .highlight-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--color-ok);
  }
  
  .highlight-box ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .highlight-box li {
    padding: var(--space-1) 0;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  
  .list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  
  .list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }
  
  .list li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.6em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  
  .update-notice {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    padding-top: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }
  
  .update-notice p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }
  
  .back-link {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }
  
  .back-link a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-2);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>

